The paper discusses the implementation and characterization of a cooperative physical layer transceiver in wireless systems, which involves techniques related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and communications (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), augmented reality (cs.AR), and multimedia (cs.MM). The focus on physical layer cooperation and real-time performance also suggests a strong likelihood of the paper belonging to cs.IT and cs.NI.
